(It also aligns with my favorite constant in the show which is basically everyone in the past’s response to Claire doing time travel being, “Well yeah those are faerie stones/Yeah Claire’s a witch we’ve known the entire time duh” okay I’m done now be about your business)

And if this show doesn’t end by presenting Claire as…idk God or some other deity-like determiner of fate I am going to sorely disappointed because that really is the best answer and also WOW WHAT A KICKASS ENDING TO A BODICE RIPPER SERIES

The other answer is that Claire Elizabeth Beauchamp Randall Fraser is a universal constant; what is, what will be, and what has been is in part determined by Claire’s presence. Frank looks like Randall because he is fated to meet Claire, he can’t have kids for the same reason.

Now the show’s view of time travel is that fate is fate, what will be will always be and always has been and you can fight against fate the same way stones fight water, so Frank looking like Randall just because he does isn’t all that strange in terms of canon I suppose.

I do not expect the show to answer these questions (I will not read the books until the show is over I do not want my show experienced influenced by book canon) but I need answers!!! This has driven me nuts since I first watched the show!!!!

WHICH MEANS THAT FRANK IS NOT RANDALL’S DIRECT DESCENDANT WHICH BEGS TWO QUESTIONS: One, why does Frank look like Randall? And two, why does he carry the clearly implied generational curse brought about by Randall being The Scum of the Earth, and Jamie’s retribution?

In this same season we also meet Mary Hawkins, who we know thanks to Frank, is Randall’s wife. We also meet Alex Randall, Jonathan’s brother. In later seasons we find out that Alex and Mary banged pre-wedding day and she is pregnant, but Alex dies and ends up married to Jonathan

When Claire and Jamie go to France, Jamie duels Randall and while he doesn’t successfully kill Randall he does quite literally stab him in the dick, this is a clear reference to the fact that Frank is sterile which we find out earlier in the same season.

In the very beginning of the show two important facts are established; Frank Randall is the direct descendent of Jonathan “Black Jack” Randall, and is also his doppelgänger. Put a pin in that this is important.

I understand that the purpose of Outlander isn’t to be a consistent narrative about the dangers of time travel and the hubris of humankind fighting against our respective fates, it’s a bodice ripper that occasionally does the previous and I love that about it I do, HOWEVER!

Hi I’ve been rewatching Outlander and I have thoughts that are absolutely pointless and in way an actual critique of the show but I am going to speak on this because I want to and I can. Spoilers ahead.

Last night I had a nightmare so bad that I woke up tossing and turning and saying no, all sweaty and shaky and gross. What was the nightmare about, you wonder, what could scare you so badly?

It was nightmare that ET was trying to give me presents. That was it. At my big age.
That's where I am. Grieving for past me and furious at the standard I was held to but could never meet because I didn't have a stupid button.

And then you find out, it's not that everyone else got to the side of the wall because they're just better than you they just had the button the entire time. No one gave you a fucking stupid little button. You'd be furious too right? So happy to have it now, but heartbroken. Mad.

In a blink, you are on the other side of the wall. You finish the task. You come across another task, wall goes up, you press the button. Bam, other side of the wall. How angry do you think you'd be? Excited too, thrilled even, to have this button. But how mad?

And after so many years you get pretty good at it, you get around the wall faster, you've made tools to make it less difficult but the wall is still there. And then one day, a nice doctor that you have spent too much money on, gives you a button. And you press the button.

And everyone in charge can just teleport to the other side of the wall too, your teachers and your bosses, your parents, they just blink and boom they can start the task, but not you. So you've been finding all kinds of tricks to get to the other side of the wall.

In order to start the task, you need to get around the wall, you could climb it, walk around it, dig through or under. All of these take immense effort. And it's every time. For every task. But nearly everyone around you can just teleport to the other side of the wall and start.

Hey for people who don't have ADHD and are perhaps confused as to why I am furious today (which is fair, you don't know what it's like) I want to imagine that every time you thought to yourself "I would like to start this task" a wall a million feet in every direction appeared

If you have a hard time hearing what your body wants/needs, set alarms. And when those go off you don’t have to like eat a meal, shove a handful of almonds in your mouth and get some juice.

With that last one, trade and barter system babey! They make you food when you’re depressed, you help them when you’re better and you can. Or you give them cuttings of your jade plant. Support each other!!!

Find friends/family who you know like to cook. They will bring you food. I am not kidding about this they will do it. If you know me, hi I’m that friend I’ll make you health potion veggie soup just let me know what’s up I’m here and I love you. So do your friends I promise.

If you’ve got the funds, order in babey!!! Again we are looking for function in a time of crisis (if you cannot function that’s a crisis you cannot change my mind on this) so Uber Eats is a good solution 10/10 highly recommend.

Get some fresh produce that you don’t need to do anything to, like spinach might be bad because you’d have to make a salad. But if you like carrots just get a bag of baby carrots. Get some bananas. Apples. Cucumbers are great so much water and you can just bite into those babies.

If cooking is something you struggle a lot with, there’s 0 shame in things like easy mac, ramen, Mrs. Grass chicken soup (a balm on the soul that last one). This is all about function. So whatever functional is for you is perfect and good.

Third thing, if you can feel you brain starting to go fuzzy, or you know it’s gonna be a bad week or whatever, prep what you can. I’ll make like a week’s worth of rice, get some frozen meat/potatoes/veg. Things you can make without having to think.

Second thing is that there are no rules. You can shove a slice of deli meat and cheese in your mouth and call it a snack. Eat an entire bag of grapes because there’s no prep required. Have a milkshake because it will bring you some joy. Get food in your body.
